    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9800</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsection id="s16018" division="truck" formnum="CTS-5232" date="01/27/1997">
        <title>CAB - TILT: 9800</title>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>9800</truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <lev1>
                    <title>GENERAL</title>
                    <para>The cab for 9800 model cabover (CO) is made of aluminum to resist corrosion and to reduce
                        vehicle weight (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1601801">Figure 1</hotlnk>). Riveted construction adds strength and improves
                        repairability. Structural sealers increase joint strength.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f1601801" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g1601801" filename="../figg16/g1601801.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                                 scalefitwidth="192px" scalefitheight="192px" resolution="72"/>
                        <caption>Figure 1. 9800 CO Cab</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <para>The combination of riveted construction and adhesive sealers provide a much tighter fitting
                        cab, which eliminates air leaks, reduces road noise and improves driver comfort.
                    </para>
                    <para>The one-piece extruded door frame provides increased strength and helps maintain proper door
                        fit (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1601802">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f1601802" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g1601802" filename="../figg16/g1601802.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                                 scalefitwidth="152px" scalefitheight="232px" resolution="72"/>
                        <caption>Figure 2. One-Piece Door Frame</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <para>
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1601803">Figure 3</hotlnk>
                        shows the two different types of 9800 cabover (CO) models. The 9800 SFA model has three
                        different cab sizes: the 63-inch day cab, 89-inch and 110-inch Pro Sleeper bumper to back of cab
                        (BBC). The 9800 SBA model has two different cab sizes: the 89-inch and 110-inch Pro Sleeper
                        bumper to back of cab (BBC). The 9800 cabover (CO) models also have two different roof designs:
                        the Flat Roof design and the Raised Roof design.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f1601803" figsize="pg-wide">
                        <graphic id="g1601803" filename="../figg16/g1601803.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                                 scalefitwidth="514px" scalefitheight="502px" resolution="72"/>
                        <caption>Figure 3. 9800 SFA and SBA Cabs</caption>
                    </figure>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <title>VEHICLE IDENTIFICATION NUMBER (VIN) TAG LOCATION</title>
                    <para>Have the VIN conveniently at hand when you service the vehicle and need service parts. The cab
                        and chassis VIN (s) are on the serial tags located on the face of the latch pillar of the cab
                        door opening, driver's side (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1601804">Figure 4</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f1601804" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g1601804" filename="../figg16/g1601804.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                                 scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
                        <caption>Figure 4. VIN Tag Location</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. CHASSIS "VIN" TAG</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. CAB "VIN" TAG</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. CAB DOOR OPENING LATCH PILLAR</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <title>WINDSHIELD WIPERS</title>
                    <para>The windshield wipers (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1601805">Figure 5</hotlnk>) are mounted below the windshield in the cab cowl
                        bar and the wiper/washer switches are located on the instrument wing panel to the right of the
                        driver.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f1601805" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g1601805" filename="../figg16/g1601805.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                                 scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
                        <caption>Figure 5. Windshield Washer System</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. NOZZLES</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. WIRE (CONTROL SWITCH-TO-MOTOR)</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. PUMP MOTOR AND RESERVOIR (IN STORAGE AREA)</callout1>
                            <callout1>4. HOSE (PUMP-TO-WIPER NOZZLE)</callout1>
                            <callout1>5. WINDSHIELD WIPERS</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <title>WINDSHIELD WASHER</title>
                    <para>The windshield washer system (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1601805">Figure 5</hotlnk>) consists of a reservoir with an integral electric
                        powered pump motor. The system will deliver washer solvent to the windshield through hoses and
                        nozzles in the wiper arms. Reservoir and pump motor are located in the storage compartment to
                        the right of driver's door. All components are available for service.
                    </para>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <title>INSTRUMENT PANEL</title>
                    <para>The instrument panel gauges are located for driver convenience (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1601806">Figure 6</hotlnk>). Instrument clusters are easily removed for access
                        to speedometer, tachometer, gauges, warning lights, bulbs, plumbing and wiring.
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f1601806" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g1601806" filename="../figg16/g1601806.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                                 scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="232px" resolution="72"/>
                        <caption>Figure 6. Instrument Panel Gauges</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <para>The instrument wing panel switches and controls are located for driver convenience and are
                        both easy to read and easy to reach (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1601807">Figure 7</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f1601807" figsize="pg-wide">
                        <graphic id="g1601807" filename="../figg16/g1601807.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                                 scalefitwidth="472px" scalefitheight="352px" resolution="72"/>
                        <caption>Figure 7. Instrument Panel Wing Panel Switches and Controls</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <para>The power distribution center is located under the center console behind the circuit panel
                        cover. This panel contains the fuses, circuit breakers, relays, flasher and warning buzzer (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1601808">Figure 8</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f1601808" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g1601808" filename="../figg16/g1601808.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                                 scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
                        <caption>Figure 8. Power Distribution Center</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. ACCESS COVER TO SWITCHES AND WIPER MOTOR</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. FUSE, RELAY, CIRCUIT PANEL COVER</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </lev1>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
